item.description:
In a Rails project I have a data model for recipes. Some recipes belong to other recipes as byproducts—for example, the recipe for &lsquo;Whey&rsquo; is a byproduct of the recipe for &lsquo;Cheese.&rsquo;
This calls for some recipe instances to have a has_many association with their byproduct recipes, which in turn have a belongs_to association back to their parent recipe.
